This is not necessarily true... The fan FRU's (/xyz/openbmc_project/inventory/system/chassis/motherboard/fan1) Functional property of "false" does not definitively mean that each of its rotors are also non-functional.

The fan FRU represents how the system's manufacturer wants to represent when that FRU is not functional. This may or may not mean that, in the case of dual rotor fans, each of the rotors are nonfunctional since it may take both rotors to be nonfunctional for the FRU to be nonfunctional OR a single nonfunctional rotor in a dual rotor fan could mean the FRU is nonfunctional.
